'''Exercise 30
In this exercise, weâ€™ll practice doing such unraveling. Write a function that takes a list of lists (just one element deep) and returns 
a flat, one-dimensional version of the list. Thus, invoking

flatten([[1,2], [3,4]])
will return

[1,2,3,4]

'''
lista = [[1,2],[3,4]]

nowa_lista = [element for sublista in lista for element in sublista]
print(nowa_lista)





